🚀 Launching an Apache Web Server on AWS EC2 (Hands-On Cloud Project)

Today I deployed a simple Apache Web Server on Amazon EC2 and served a custom HTML page. This was a great exercise to practice working with Linux, SSH, and security groups in the cloud.

🔧 Steps I Followed

1️⃣ Launch an EC2 Instance

- AMI: Amazon Linux
- Instance Type: t2.micro (Free Tier)
- Create or select a **Key Pair**

Created and downloaded a key pair for SSH access

2️⃣ Configure Security Group
To allow users to access the website, I added an Inbound Rule:
Add an inbound rule:

| Type | Protocol | Port | Source |
|-----|-----|-----|-----|
| HTTP | TCP | 80 | 0.0.0.0/0 |

This allows traffic from the internet to reach the web server.

3️⃣ Connect to the Instance (AWS Linux CLI)

📝 Editing Files with VIM
To manually edit the web page on the server:

sudo vim /var/www/html/index.html
Basic VIM workflow:
Press i → enter insert mode
Edit the file
Press ESC
Type → save and exit


